data.value: Sets the maximum size of avatar images in pixels.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.boardaccess
data.value: Specifies the message board security access level. This property is only applied when the first message is posted. You can later change the properties in CMS Desk -> Tools -> Message boards.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.boarddisplayname
data.value: Board display name. You can also use macros for the name. This property is only applied when the first message is posted. You can later change the properties in CMS Desk -> Tools -> Message boards.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.boardenablesubs
data.value: Indicates whether the subscription feature should be enabled. This property is only applied after the first message is posted. You can later change the properties in CMS Desk -> Tools -> Message boards.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.boardmoderated
data.value: Indicates whether the board is moderated or not. This property is only applied when the first message is posted. You can later change the properties in CMS Desk -> Tools -> Message boards.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.boardmoderators
data.value: Selects which users will be designated as moderators for the newly created message board. This property is only applied when the first message is posted. You can later change the properties in CMS Desk -> Tools -> Message boards.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.boardopen
data.value: Indicates whether the board should be opened (i.e. new messages can be added) by default. This property is only applied when the first message is posted. You can later change the properties in CMS Desk -> Tools -> Message boards.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.boardopenfrom
data.value: Board opening date. This property is only applied when the first message is posted. You can later change the properties in CMS Desk -> Tools -> Message boards.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.boardopento
data.value: Board closing date. This property is only applied when the first message is posted. You can later change the properties in CMS Desk -> Tools -> Message boards.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.boardowner
data.value: Specifies the owner of newly created message board. This property cannot be changed once the board is created.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.boardroles
data.value: Sets the roles that will be authorized to post on the newly created message board by default. This property is only applied when the first message is posted. You can later change the properties in CMS Desk -> Tools -> Message boards.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.boardunsubscriptionurl
data.value: URL of the page used to unsubscribe from the subscribed message board. If it is not specified, default unsubscription URL from Site Manager -> Settings -> Community -> Message boards is used. This property is only applied when the first message is posted. You can later change the properties in CMS Desk -> Tools -> Message boards.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.cacheitemname
data.value: Sets the name of the cache key used for the content of the web part. If not specified, this name is generated automatically based on the site, document path, Web part control ID and current user. A cache key can be shared between multiple web parts with the same content on different pages in order to avoid keeping redundant data in the memory.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.cacheminutes
data.value: Sets the number of minutes for which the content of the web part should remain cached before its latest version is reloaded from the database. If left empty, the value entered into the Site Manager -> Settings -> System -> Performance -> Cache content (minutes) setting will be used instead. If set to 0, caching will be disabled for the web part.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.captchatext
data.value: Sets the text displayed before the verification field where users have to enter the content of the CAPTCHA image.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.checkperm
data.value: Indicates if the permissions of the current user should be checked for the content of the web part. If enabled, only documents for which the user has the "read" permission will be loaded.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.columns
data.value: Lists the database columns which should be loaded along with the given objects, separated by commas (,). If empty, all columns will be loaded. Specifying a list without unnecessary columns may significantly improve performance.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.combinewithculture
data.value: Indicates if the default language version of a document should be used as a replacement if a given document is not translated to the currently selected language. If the 'Use site settings' option is selected, the value is taken from 'Site Manager -> Settings -> Content -> Combine with default culture'.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.container
data.value: Specifies the name of the container (box) to be displayed around the web part. Only containers defined in Site Manager -> Development -> Web part containers can be selected. The selected container can be edited directly by using the Edit button.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.containertitle
data.value: Sets a title for the container. This title is displayed only if the {%ContainerTitle%} macro is used in the code of the container.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.contentafter
data.value: HTML content placed after the web part. Can be used to display a footer or close the tags contained in the ContentBefore value, such as or elements.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.contentbefore
data.value: HTML content placed before the web part. Can be used to display a header or add some encapsulating code, such as <div> or <table> elements to achieve the required layout.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.cssprefix
data.value: Through this property, you can set different CSS styles for individual menu levels. Enter the prefixes of the CSS classes that should be applied, starting from the first menu level and separated by semicolons (;).

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.culturecode
data.value: Indicates which culture version of the specified documents should be used.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.currentpage
data.value: Sets the transformation used for the currently selected page. Use <%# Eval("Page") %> to get the current page number, <%# Eval("PageURL") %> to get the page URL or <%# Eval("PageLink") %> to get a link to the current page.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.customtimezone
data.value: May be used to assign a custom time zone specifically for the content of this web part. If selected, the time zone will be used regardless of current user or website time zone settings.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.datasourcename
data.value: Must contain the Web part control ID of the data source web part which provides the objects to be displayed. The data source web part must be placed on the same page.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.department
data.value: Department of products which should be displayed.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.disablefiltercaching
data.value: Indicates if caching should be disabled for the data contained in the connected source. This should only be used in special cases where the displayed data is not being refreshed by the filter.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.disableviewstate
data.value: Indicates if view state should be disabled for this web part.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.display
data.value: Determines if link should be displayed or stay hidden.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.displaycaptcha
data.value: Indicates if a CAPTCHA security check should be required before allowing users to subscribe to a newsletter.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.displayfirstlastautomatically
data.value: If enabled, the "go to first page" and "go to last page" buttons of the pager will be displayed only when there is no other way to access the first or last page through the pager.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.displaymode
data.value: Sets the mode used to display forum posts if the Forum layout property is set to Tree. Possible options are: Tree mode - the details of the selected post are displayed above the tree. Detail mode - post details are displayed inside the tree for all expanded nodes. Dynamic detail mode - post details are displayed inside the tree for selected nodes.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.displaypreviousnextautomatically
data.value: If enabled, the "go to previous page" and "go to next page" buttons of the pager will be displayed only when there is no other way of accessing the previous or next page through the pager.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.displaytoroles
data.value: Contains a list of roles to which the web part should be displayed. This may be used to implement documents with specific functionality for different types of users. The roles in the list must be specified by their code names and separated by semicolons (;). If empty, the web part will be displayed to all users.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.documenttypes
data.value: Determines which document types should be loaded, specified by a list of code names separated by semicolons (;). The * wildcard can be used as a substitute for a random sequence of characters. For example Product.* would include document types such as Product.Camera, Product.CellPhone, Product.Computer etc. If left empty, the web part will retrieve all document types by default. Please note that in this case (empty value), only the common data columns from View_CMS_Tree_Joined will be available. The specific fields of individual document types will not be included, so please consider this when writing transformations, WHERE conditions etc.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.edititemtransform
data.value: The transformation for the item selected for editing in the datalist.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.enableanonymread
data.value: Indicates whether the anonymous read is enabled

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.enablecontentrating
data.value: If checked, content rating is enabled.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.enablepaging
data.value: Indicates if the displayed data should be paged.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.enablesubs
data.value: Indicates whether the subscription feature should be enabled.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.enableviewstate
data.value: Indicates if ViewState should be enabled.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.filesfilter
data.value: Can be used to enter an expression to filter which files should be included in the data source. The * wildcard may be used to indicate any number of characters. For example: "*.*", "*.jpg" "*.jpg;*.gif"

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.filterduplicates
data.value: Indicates if the retrieved data should be filtered to contain documents only once, even if they are linked multiple times.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.filtername
data.value: Sets the name of the Filter web part that should be connected.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.firstpage
data.value: Sets the transformation used for the link to the first page. Use <%# Eval("FirstURL") %> to get the URL of the first page.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.footertransform
data.value: Sets the transformation placed at the end of the list of displayed items. Transformations are specified in format <class name>.<transformation name>.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.groupname
data.value: Selects which group should be used by the web part.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.headertransform
data.value: Sets the transformation placed before the list of displayed items. Transformations are specified in format <class name>.<transformation name>.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.hidenofound
data.value: Indicates if the web part should be hidden when no items to be displayed are retrieved.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.hideonsub
data.value: Indicates if the web part should be hidden on sub-pages. If checked, the web part will not be displayed on documents that inherit the web part from a parent document.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.highlightallpath
data.value: Indicates if all items in the currently selected path of the menu control should be displayed as highlighted.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.highlightedpath
data.value: Alias path of the node that should be selected in the menu control. If you do not specify any value, the current path is used.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.id
data.value: Serves as an identifier for the web part. This ID must be unique within the context of each page template. The value of this property may only contain alphanumeric characters and the underscore character ( _ ).

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.itemseparator
data.value: Contains the code of a separator to be placed between displayed items, e.g. <hr />.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.joingroupurl
data.value: Selects the document to which users will be redirected if the group only allows group members to view its content. A link to this URL can be added to the text displayed by the web part by entering the following expression into the Group members only text (site members) property: {0}Link text{1}

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.lastpage
data.value: Sets the transformation used for the link to the last page. Use <%# Eval("LastURL") %> to get the URL of the last page.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.loginurl
data.value: Sets the URL where public users will be redirected if the group is not accessible to them. A link to this URL can be added to the text displayed by the web part by entering the following expression into the text Site/Group members only text properties: {0}Link text{1}

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.maindoc
data.value: Sets the document for which related documents will be displayed. Either the current document is used, or another document can be specified by entering its NodeGUID. Please note that if relationships are used, only the documents defined by the relationship settings will be displayed.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.mainonleft
data.value: If checked, documents on the right side of the relationship with the specified document will be displayed.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.maxnestinglevel
data.value: Specifies the maximum number of content tree sub-levels from which content should be loaded. This number is relative, i.e. counted from the start of the path specified for the content of the web part. Entering -1 causes all sub-levels to be included.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.maxratingvalue
data.value: Sets size of the content rating scale.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.nestedcontrolsid
data.value: Must contain the IDs of any nested controls, separated by semicolons (;). For example: myRepeaterID;myDatalistID;myRepeaterID2. This property replaces the previously used NestedRepeaterID and NestedDataListID properties. If you are still using these properties, no changes to functionality will occur, but it is advisable to rewrite your code to use the new property instead. If you need to dynamically set the properties of a nested control, you have to set its DelayedLoading property to 'True'. Please note that this setting can cause problems with ViewState.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.nesteddatalist
data.value: ID of the nested CMSDataList control as you specify it in the transformation code.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.nestedrepeater
data.value: ID of the nested CMSRepeater control as you specify it in the transformation code.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.newbtntext
data.value: Sets the description text for the New document button.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.nextgroup
data.value: Sets the transformation used for the link to the next group of page links. Use <%# Eval("NextGroupURL") %> to get the URL of the next group.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.nextpage
data.value: Sets the transformation used for the link to the next page. Use <%# Eval("NextURL") %> to get the URL of the next page.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.nomessagestext
data.value: Text displayed when there are no messages to be displayed.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.noprofiletext
data.value: Text that will be displayed if no profile is found.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.norecordtext
data.value: Text that should be displayed if no records are found. This text will not be visible if the Hide if no record found property of the web part is enabled.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.nrandomproducts
data.value: Indicates how many random products should be displayed. Don't put any value, if you want display all products.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.orderby
data.value: Sets the value of the ORDER BY clause in the SELECT statement used to retrieve the content.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.pagerlayout
data.value: Sets the transformation that determines the overall design of the pager.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.pagerposition
data.value: Determines if the pager is displayed above or below the content displayed by the web part.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.pages
data.value: Sets the transformation used for page links. Use <%# Eval("Page") %> to get the appropriate page number dynamically, <%# Eval("PageURL") %> to get the page URL or <%# Eval("PageLink") %> to get a link to the appropriate page.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.pageseparator
data.value: Sets the transformation used as a separator between page links.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.pagesize
data.value: Determines the maximum number of records displayed per page.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.pagingmode
data.value: Determines which method is used to pass information about the currently selected page - it can be passed either as a parameter in the URL (Query string) or through postback (Postback).

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.path
data.value: Specifies the path of the documents that should be selected. If empty, the path will be set to all child documents under the page on which the web part is placed. Use '.' for current document selection.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.previousgroup
data.value: Sets the transformation used for the link to the previous group of page links. Use <%# Eval("PreviousGroupURL") %> to get the URL of the previous group.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.previouspage
data.value: Sets the transformation used for the link to the previous page. Use <%# Eval("PreviousURL") %> to get the URL of the previous page.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.productpublicstatus
data.value: Public status of products which should be displayed.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.query
data.value: Name of the query to be used for retrieving data from Kentico CMS Database. The queries can be defined in Site Manager -> Document types -> edit a document type -> Queries.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.queryname
data.value: Sets the name of the predefined SQL query that should be used to retrieve the data. Queries are specified in format <class name>.<query name>.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.querystring
data.value: Sets the name of the URL parameter used to pass information about the current page number (used if the Paging mode property is set to Query string).

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.ratingtype
data.value: Determines which type of content rating will be used.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.ratingvalue
data.value: This property could be used to preset rating value. If it is not set then current document rating value is used. Rating value must be a number from the interval <0, 1>.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.relationship
data.value: Allows the selection of the document relationship that should be used.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.requireemail
data.value: Indicates whether the board message requires e-mail address. This property is only applied when the first message is posted. You can later change the properties in CMS Desk -> Tools -> Message boards.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.selecteditemtransformation
data.value: The transformation for the selected item in the datalist.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.selectedtransf
data.value: Sets the transformation to be used for the displayed content in detail view mode. Transformations are specified in format <class name>.<transformation name>.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.selecthidden
data.value: Determines if hidden users should be included.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.selectonlyapproved
data.value: Indicates if only approved items should be selected.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.selectpublished
data.value: Indicates if only published documents should be loaded.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.selecttopn
data.value: Specifies the maximum amount of items to be selected. If empty, all possible items are selected.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.separatortransform
data.value: Sets the transformation used to separate the displayed items. Transformations are specified in format <class name>.<transformation name>.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.showapprove
data.value: Indicates whether the message APPROVE button should be displayed

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.showdelete
data.value: Indicates whether the message DELETE button should be displayed

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.showedit
data.value: Indicates whether the message EDIT button should be displayed

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.showeditdelete
data.value: If enabled, the web part offers edit and delete buttons for each item when displaying the page in edit mode. You can set the exact position of the buttons by adding the ##editbuttons## macro into the code of the used item transformation (must be of the ASCX type).

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.showemail
data.value: Indicates whether the e-mail should be displayed

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.showfilter
data.value: Indicates whether a filter should be displayed above the list of items.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.showfirstlast
data.value: Indicates if the buttons used for navigating to the first and last page should be displayed.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.showfordocumenttypes
data.value: Contains a list of document types on which the web part should be displayed. If the currently selected document uses the page template containing this web part, but its type is not specified by this property, the web part will be hidden. The document types in the list must be specified by their code names and separated by semicolons (;). If empty, the web part will be displayed on all document types.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.shownewbtn
data.value: Indicates if the button for adding new documents should be displayed when viewing the page in edit mode. When the button is used, a document of the first type entered into the Document types property is created at the beginning of the path specified for the web part's content.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.showreject
data.value: Indicates whether the message REJECT button should be displayed

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.sitename
data.value: Sets the website (specified by its code name) from which the content should be loaded. If left empty, the current site is used.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.startingaliaspath
data.value: Sets the alias path of the document that will serve as the root of the content tree in CMS Desk -> Content for users who register through the web part. The users will only be able to access the given document and its child documents. Please note that this only affects the CMS Desk editing interface and not the live site.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.submenuindicator
data.value: Contains the path to the image that is used to indicate that menu items contain further sub-items. For example: ~/App_Themes/Site/Images/submenu.gif

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.timezonetype
data.value: Specifies the type of time zone used for the content of the web part.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.transformation
data.value: Sets the transformation used for the displayed content in list view mode. Transformations are specified in format <class name>.<transformation name>.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.unsubscriptionurl
data.value: URL used to unsubscribe from the subscribed issue

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.username
data.value: Name of a user to be displayed.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.usesecuritycode
data.value: Indicates whether the board uses the security CAPTCHA feature. This property is only applied when the first message is posted. You can later change the properties in CMS Desk -> Tools -> Message boards.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.useupdatepanel
data.value: Indicates if an AJAX UpdatePanel container should be used for this web part.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.visibilityformname
data.value: Can be used to select from which form visibility settings should be loaded if the Apply visibility settings property is enabled. If empty, the form specified in the Form name property will be used.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.visible
data.value: Indicates if the web part should be displayed.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.webserviceparameters
data.value: Can be used to enter a string value that will be passed to the web service as a parameter.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.webserviceurl
data.value: Specifies the URL of the web service that will provide the data. For example: http://localhost/webservice1/Service.asmx

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.where
data.value: Sets the value of the WHERE clause in the SELECT statement used to retrieve the content.

data.name: documentation.webpartproperties.xmlurl
data.value: Specifies the URL of the XML document from which the data will be loaded. The URL can be absolute or relative from the root of the current website.

data.name: documentselection.rootselected
data.value: You can't select the website. Please select a document.

data.value: Please enter transformation name in identifier format.

data.value: Please enter document type code name in identifier format.

data.value: Please enter a document type code name.
